body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
```
module test2;
    typedef struct {
        struct {
            struct {
                logic [31:0] next;
            } val;
        } el[1];
    } field_combo_t;
    field_combo_t field_combo;
endmodule
```

`/tools/work/verilator_compile/5.10/bin/verilator_bin --build --cc ../test2.sv`
```
Segmentation fault (core dumped)
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
`Verilator 5.011 devel rev v5.010-25-g76f5de6e5`
But I tried also 5.006 tag

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

Yes I can give it a try if I get some directions.

Running this with --structs-packed solves the segmentation fault, but then I have different error in different part of design.
```
typedef struct {
    logic [31:0] value;
} base_struct;

typedef struct {
    base_struct el[1];
} top_struct;

module test ;
    top_struct fails;
    assign fails.el[0].value = 32'd1;
endmodule
```
```
%Error: Internal Error: ../test.sv:10:16: ../V3Dfg.h:537: DfgVertex is not of expected type, but instead has type 'VARPACKED'
   10 |     top_struct fails;
```

Which is I guess ok, as this doesnt also work on other simulators if these two are packed
